Bill Wood wrote:

> Rats!  I fat-fingered the original post with this subject big time; my
> apologies.  Of course, I'm interested in asking this community about
> OCaml on Debian or Ubuntu.

I use Ocaml on both a Debian testing machine and on Ubuntu machines.

Since I run the Testing version of Debian, I find that the libraries
can be a little more up-to-date that Ubuntu while Ubuntu is a little
more polished that Debian.

Ocaml is supported so well on these platforms that I rarely need to
download anything and install it from source.


